There are just <i>so</i> many things wrong with this article I don't know where to start.  I've seen at least one error, one incorrect description, and this code:<p><pre><code>    if ((number & -number) == number) {
        return true;
    }
    return false;
</code></pre>
It would be a more interesting interview question to get a candidate to analyze these examples, rather than trying to solve the problem.
